The Managing Director, Genesis Group of Companies, Nnaeto Orazulike, has been honoured by the Nigerian Association of Chambers of Commerce, Industry, Mines, and Agriculture awarding committee with the Excellence Award for his contribution to the hospitality and entertainment industry. The award was presented by the National President, NACCIMA, Hajiya Saratu Aliyu at the association’s anniversary celebration in Abuja, recently. According to a statement, Orazulike had played an exemplary role in the entertainment and hospitality sector, having established businesses and structures around the state. “Orazulike had been responsible for the many fun days and moments Nigerians had and memories shared before the great pandemic hit,” it stated. He holds a B.Sc. in accountancy from the University of Nigeria, Nsukka. He began private business in 1993 when he started Genesis Foods Limited and had grown into a force to reckon with, as front liners in the industrial catering services company. His vast chain of other successful businesses includes Orazilike Trading Company Limited; Stanchions Nigeria Limited and Genesis Deluxe Cinemas Limited. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com